Former State Security Minister David Mahlobo has denied any involvement in the removal of former President Jacob Zuma’s estranged wife from his residential house in Nkandla. Mahlobo was testifying at the State Capture Commission in Johannesburg on Wednesday. He also denied recruiting a former State Security Agency member to mitigate the Fees Must Fall movement. Video: State Capture Inquiry | Matshela Koko, David Mahlobo testify 